# Vue 3 + Nuxt 4 Patterns

## Composition API and script setup

- Use `<script setup lang="ts">` for all components
- Prefer Composition API: `ref`, `computed`, `watch`, `onMounted`, etc.
- Nuxt auto-imports Vue APIs and Nuxt composables; avoid redundant imports unless needed for clarity or types

## Components

- Place components in `app/components/` (or `components/`); Nuxt auto-imports them
- Use PascalCase for component names in templates

## Composables

- Place in `app/composables/` with named export `useXxx`; they are auto-imported
- Use for shared reactive logic and Nuxt-specific helpers (e.g. `useState`, `useFetch`)

## State

- Prefer Pinia stores for global state
- Use `useState` for SSR-friendly, request-scoped state when appropriate

## Data fetching

- **Firestore:** Use VueFire `useCollection` / `useDocument` for real-time Firestore data (auto-imported by nuxt-vuefire). See firebase-vuefire rule.
- **Nitro API / non-Firestore:** Prefer `useFetch` / `useAsyncData` for SSR-safe data loading
- Use `server/api/` and `defineEventHandler` for backend logic (Nitro)

## Routing

- File-based routing under `app/pages/`
- Use `<NuxtLink>` for links; use `navigateTo`, `useRouter`, `useRoute` when needed

## Server

- API routes in `server/api/`; server middleware in `server/middleware/`
- Use `defineEventHandler`, `readBody`, `getQuery`, etc. (Nitro/h3)

## Tailwind

- Prefer utility classes in template
- Avoid `@apply` in Vue `<style>` unless necessary and with clear scoping (see Nuxt 4 + Tailwind docs)

## Environment and config

- Use `useRuntimeConfig()` and Nitro env as needed; never hardcode secrets
